---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Musical Terms Valid in Scrabble — Notes, Tempo & Instruments"
  description="Explore 18 musical terms valid in Scrabble with point values. From WALTZ to FUGUE, master music vocabulary that scores big. Italian-origin words, instruments, and tempo markings."
  keywords="musical terms scrabble, music words scrabble, scrabble music vocabulary, waltz scrabble points, instrument words scrabble, tempo words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Musical Terms Valid in Scrabble — Notes, Tempo & Instruments",
    "description": "Explore 18 musical terms valid in Scrabble with point values and strategy tips for playing music vocabulary.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/musical-terms-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the highest-scoring music word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WALTZ scores 17 points (W4+A1+L1+T1+Z10) thanks to both W (4 pts) and Z (10 pts). HYMN scores 12 points (H4+Y4+M3+N1) as the second highest among common musical terms. CHORD and CHIME both score well at 11 and 12 points respectively." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are Italian music terms valid in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Many Italian music terms are valid because they've been adopted into English. FORTE, TEMPO, RONDO, and FUGUE are all playable. However, some Italian terms like PIANISSIMO may not be in all dictionaries. Check your game's dictionary (TWL or SOWPODS) for specific terms." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is WALTZ a good Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "WALTZ is excellent — it scores 17 points base (W4+A1+L1+T1+Z10) and uses the Z tile effectively with common letters. It can also be extended to WALTZED (23 pts) or WALTZING. On a Triple Word Score, WALTZ alone scores 51 points." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Music</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Musical Terms Valid in Scrabble — Notes, Tempo & Instruments</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        Music and Scrabble share a surprising connection: both reward those who know specialized vocabulary. Italian tempo markings, instrument names, compositional forms, and dance styles have all entered the English dictionary — and many score remarkably well thanks to uncommon letter combinations. From WALTZ with its Z tile to HYMN's compact power, musical terms deserve a place in every serious player's repertoire.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (WALTZ)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9.3</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4.8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Length</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 18 Musical Terms for Scrabble</h2>
      <p>All words below are valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. The list includes Italian-origin terms, instrument names, dance forms, and general music vocabulary — sorted by point value.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Breakdown</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Category</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">WALTZ</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">W4+A1+L1+T1+Z10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Dance</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HYMN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">H4+Y4+M3+N1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Vocal</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHIME</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">12</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">C3+H4+I1+M3+E1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Percussion</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CHORD</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">C3+H4+O1+R1+D2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Theory</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">POLKA</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">P3+O1+L1+K5+A1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Dance</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OCTAVE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">11</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">O1+C3+T1+A1+V4+E1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Theory</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">LYRIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">L1+Y4+R1+I1+C3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Vocal</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">THRUM</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">T1+H4+R1+U1+M3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">String</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">FUGUE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">F4+U1+G2+U1+E1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Form</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">CLEF</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">C3+L1+E1+F4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">Notation</td></tr>
